node.text:
This guy is wonderful and it makes me sick to my stomach when he talks about the things that he saw that day. The worst possible people stormed the Capitol on January 6th. Privileged, entitled, and presumptuous that they were just going to walk in and no one would try to stop them.

Turns out every officer there wasn’t the kind of officer that would remove  barricades for them and unlock doors. They were enough of those, but I’m thankful this guy wasn’t one of them. But it sure sounds like they put them through hell.

node.text:
A, that woman is an absolute queen.

B, I wish someone would tell me to get back on my highway to hell, just once. I would fall over laughing right in front of them. That’s hilarious and the fact he’s about to have a coronary because they were short on baskets, is just beyond..

node.title: Get back on your highway to hell! 🤣

node.text:
Nobody wants you to be a white savior, but if you can stand while you’re being celebrated and speak the obvious truth, that nobody seems to be speaking, there’s beauty in that. She’s right.

And the fact that this happened 15 days ago and it’s just sort of making the rounds now, sort of outside the sporting world, shows you truth in what she’s talking about. #PaigeBueckers

There is only one reason you say something like that out loud in a room full of people and that is because you know that you’re in a place where it will be accepted. 

It is disgusting language and behavior and the fact that the man who is speaking at the podium didn’t even flinch when it happened, and he still vouched for that guy, tells you everything you need to know. The good people in that community are out numbered. #Alabama #TommyBryant

node.text:
What Bryan Stevenson and the @eji_org are doing, not only in Montgomery, but around the country, is amazing. If you don’t know much about @eji_org, please look into them. Entrance to the Legacy Museum and the Memorial for Peace and Justice, is free. But there is a donation box inside the lobby in the Museum where you can donate money to help them continue their work. You can also donate through @eji_org 

This isn’t just about slavery, it’s also about segregation and mass incarceration. If you look into the innocent people the Equal Justice Initiative has gotten out of prison, off of death row, and read their stories, it is astounding. I think they’re just under 200. Start with Anthony Ray Hinton, who is represented in the museum. #EJI

I had someone in my DMs today yell at me because I was telling people that vaccinated folks could not spread Covid. I never thought that, and I never said that. I’m confused as to why people thought if you had the vaccine, that you couldn’t spread Covid. You can still get Covid and the Delta variant even if you’ve been vaccinated, no one said you couldn’t. node.text:
I’ve been asked several times to do a collab but until now, I never agreed. However, after a post from last week (I’ll put it in my stories) where someone felt the need to announce their departure, I was asked by @liveabove.co if I was interested, and I immediately said yes! I agreed because, I love everything they do and because this ended up being a pretty funny moment. 

These shirts were designed by @liveabove.co and the proceeds will go to benefit @crcnashville who are amazing, and they do so much to help the ppl of Nashville. Volunteering there, pre-Covid, is one of the things I miss the most. On more than one occasion, I got to see firsthand how much they help the community, especially after the tornadoes we had.

Please go check out @liveabove.co and help us raise some money for charity! I put the link in my stories and as always, I will share it on Twitter @AGirlHasNoPres 

Thank you! #LiveAbove 

They’re taking pre-orders at the link in my bio. 

*I am not a flu bot

node.text: I love her. I wish her the absolute best! I can imagine she feels like the weight of the entire team and her country is on her shoulders. That’s a lot. No matter what happens with that gymnastics team, they always go straight to her as a reason for why they did  well or not so great. She is an absolute champion. #SimoneBiles

node.text:
This guy is wonderful and it makes me sick to my stomach when he talks about the things that he saw that day. The worst possible people stormed the Capitol on January 6th. Privileged, entitled, and presumptuous that they were just going to walk in and no one would try to stop them.

Turns out every officer there wasn’t the kind of officer that would remove  barricades for them and unlock doors. They were enough of those, but I’m thankful this guy wasn’t one of them. But it sure sounds like they put them through hell.

node.text: I don’t know if you’ve been watching any of this coverage, but these things they’re saying, are absolutely awful. Listening to these guys talk about everything that happened that day. Nobody that stormed the Capitol on the January 6th, gets to say they’re from the law and order party anymore.
